@SpringBootApplication

This one annotation is enough to start and auto-configure everything in Spring Boot.

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;

@SpringBootApplication
public class MyApplication {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(MyApplication.class, args);
    }
}

@Controller
it is used to build web application and retuns HTML page and JSP it does not return JSON by default 

example: 
@Controller
 public class cont{
    GetMapping("/home")
    public static hcont{
        return "home";
    }
}

@RestController
it used to build Rest API's and it is a combination of contoller+responsebody by default retuns JSON values.
example: 
@RestController
    public class homerestcontoller{
        GetMapping("/home)
        public static rcontoller{
            return "home";
        }
    }


@Service
@Repository
@Autowired
@GetMapping
@PostMapping
@Entity
@Id
@Transactional